---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import NavBar from '../components/NavBar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { calculators, categories } from '../data/calculators';
---

<Layout
  title="About Us — Yard Metric"
  description="Yard Metric provides free, accurate material calculators for construction, landscaping, and DIY projects. Learn about our mission and how our calculators work."
  canonical="https://yardmetric.com/about/"
>
  <NavBar />

  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container">
        <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/" class="breadcrumb-link">Home</a>
          <span class="breadcrumb-sep">/</span>
          <span class="breadcrumb-current">About</span>
        </nav>
        <h1 class="page-title">About Yard Metric</h1>
        <p class="page-lead">
          We build free, fast material calculators for homeowners, contractors, landscapers,
          and builders who need accurate quantity estimates without the friction.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container content-layout">
        <div class="content-body">

          <h2>Our Mission</h2>
          <p>
            Getting material quantities wrong is expensive. Overordering wastes money and creates disposal problems.
            Underordering causes project delays and emergency rush orders. Most existing calculator sites were built years
            ago with poor mobile experiences, outdated designs, and formulas that haven't been verified against current
            industry standards.
          </p>
          <p>
            Yard Metric exists to be the best free material calculation tool on the internet, built with
            modern web technology, verified formulas, and a design that works as well on a phone at a job site as it
            does on a desktop at home.
          </p>

          <h2>How Our Calculators Work</h2>
          <p>
            Every calculator on this site uses industry-standard formulas. Volume calculators use the standard
            formula: <strong>Volume (cu yd) = Length × Width × Depth (in) ÷ 324</strong>. Weight estimates use
            material-specific bulk density values sourced from manufacturer specifications and construction industry
            references. Coverage calculators (paint, tile, drywall) use standard trade coverage rates.
          </p>
          <p>
            All calculations happen instantly in your browser; there are no server requests, no delays, and no data
            is sent anywhere. Your inputs are saved locally in your browser's localStorage for convenience and are
            never transmitted to our servers.
          </p>

          <h2>What We Cover</h2>
          <div class="cats-grid">
            {categories.map((cat) => {
              const count = calculators.filter(c => c.categorySlug === cat.slug).length;
              return (
                <a href={`/${cat.slug}/`} class="cat-card">
                  <span aria-hidden="true">{cat.icon}</span>
                  <div>
                    <p class="cat-name">{cat.name}</p>
                    <p class="cat-count">{count} calculators</p>
                  </div>
                </a>
              );
            })}
          </div>

          <h2>Accuracy &amp; Limitations</h2>
          <p>
            Our calculators are designed for estimating purposes. Real-world material quantities depend on factors
            that no calculator can fully account for: ground irregularities, compaction rates, material moisture
            content, installation technique, and supplier-specific material weights.
          </p>
          <p>
            We always recommend adding a 5–10% overage factor to any material order. Our calculators include a
            configurable waste factor for exactly this reason. Always verify quantities with your material supplier
            before placing large orders.
          </p>

          <h2>Privacy &amp; No Tracking</h2>
          <p>
            We do not collect personal information. We do not require accounts. We do not sell data.
            We do not use invasive advertising. Your calculation history stays in your browser and never leaves
            your device. See our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a> for full details.
          </p>

          <h2>Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Have a suggestion for a new calculator, found an error in a formula, or want to report a bug?
            We'd love to hear from you. Visit our <a href="/contact/">Contact page</a> to get in touch.
          </p>

        </div>

        <aside class="content-aside">
          <div class="aside-card">
            <p class="aside-label">By the Numbers</p>
            <div class="stats">
              <div class="stat-item">
                <span class="stat-n">{calculators.length}</span>
                <span class="stat-l">Free calculators</span>
              </div>
              <div class="stat-item">
                <span class="stat-n">{categories.length}</span>
                <span class="stat-l">Categories</span>
              </div>
              <div class="stat-item">
                <span class="stat-n">$0</span>
                <span class="stat-l">Cost to use</span>
              </div>
              <div class="stat-item">
                <span class="stat-n">0</span>
                <span class="stat-l">Sign-ups required</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="aside-card">
            <p class="aside-label">Quick Links</p>
            <ul class="aside-links">
              <li><a href="/">All Calculators</a></li>
              <li><a href="/landscaping/">Landscaping</a></li>
              <li><a href="/construction/">Construction</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pavers-outdoor/">Pavers &amp; Outdoor</a></li>
              <li><a href="/lumber-woodworking/">Lumber &amp; Woodworking</a></li>
              <li><a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a></li>
              <li><a href="/terms/">Terms of Use</a></li>
              <li><a href="/contact/">Contact</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
.container { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; }
.section { padding: 64px 0 80px; }
.hero { background: var(--color-canvas); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-hairline); padding: 40px 0 48px; }
.breadcrumb { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; font-size: 12px; color: var(--color-mute); margin-bottom: 24px; }
.breadcrumb-link { color: var(--color-body); text-decoration: none; }
.breadcrumb-link:hover { color: var(--color-ink); }
.breadcrumb-sep { color: var(--color-hairline-strong); }
.breadcrumb-current { color: var(--color-ink); font-weight: 500; }
.page-title { font-size: 40px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -1.8px; color: var(--color-ink); margin-bottom: 12px; }
.page-lead { font-size: 18px; color: var(--color-body); line-height: 28px; max-width: 560px; }

.content-layout { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 260px; gap: 48px; align-items: start; }
.content-body h2 { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.8px; color: var(--color-ink); margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.content-body h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
.content-body p { font-size: 15px; color: var(--color-body); line-height: 26px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
.content-body a { color: var(--color-link); }
.content-body strong { color: var(--color-ink); }

.cats-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 10px; margin: 16px 0; }
.cat-card { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; background: var(--color-canvas-soft); border-radius: 8px; padding: 12px 14px; text-decoration: none; border: 1px solid var(--color-hairline); transition: all 0.15s; font-size: 20px; }
.cat-card:hover { border-color: var(--color-hairline-strong); background: var(--color-canvas); }
.cat-name { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink); margin-bottom: 2px; }
.cat-count { font-size: 12px; color: var(--color-mute); }

.aside-card { background: var(--color-canvas); border-radius: 10px; padding: 16px; box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgba(0,0,0,0.07); margin-bottom: 16px; }
.aside-label { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--color-mute); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.stats { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }
.stat-item { text-align: center; padding: 10px; background: var(--color-canvas-soft); border-radius: 6px; }
.stat-n { display: block; font-size: 22px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.8px; color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 4px; }
.stat-l { font-size: 11px; color: var(--color-mute); }
.aside-links { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2px; }
.aside-links a { display: block; padding: 5px 8px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--color-body); text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.12s; }
.aside-links a:hover { background: var(--color-canvas-soft-2); color: var(--color-ink); }

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .content-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .content-aside { display: none; }
  .page-title { font-size: 32px; }
}
@media (max-width: 600px) { .container { padding: 0 16px; } }

/* ── Dark mode overrides ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  :global(html:not([data-theme="light"])) .aside-card { box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.07); }
}
:global(html[data-theme="dark"]) .aside-card { box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.07); }
</style>
